at it means to \"replay the same stimulus.\"\nagent_tickets/milestone_8a_canonical_stimulus_library_tickets.md:147:The milestone’s done-when clause explicitly says stimuli must be recordable and replayable, but the repo currently has no standard workflow that turns a resolved stimulus spec into a reusable local artifact. A developer could rerun the generator code manually, yet there is no deterministic output directory, no static preview artifact, no replay harness, and no guarantee that \"the same stimulus\" today will still mean the same thing when Milestone 8B or later experiment runs depend on it.\nagent_tickets/milestone_8a_canonical_stimulus_library_tickets.md:150:Add a script-thin recording and replay workflow that consumes a canonical stimulus spec, writes a reusable local stimulus bundle, and generates an offline preview artifact. The workflow should serialize the metadata needed for exact reuse, persist either the canonical cached frame sequence or the documented hybrid representation chosen in `FW-M8A-001`, and provide a replay path that can drive later retinal or experiment code without recomputing semantics ad hoc. Output paths should be deterministic, and the preview should make it easy to inspect timing and spatial content for one or more representative frames.\nagent_tickets/milestone_8a_canonical_stimulus_library_tickets.md:156:- A static preview artifact is generated in a review-friendly format such as Markdown plus images, HTML, or another lightweight offline format.\ntests/test_wave_structure_analysis.py:26:    build_simulator_extension_artifact_record,\ntests/test_wave_structure_analysis.py:59:            synchrony[\"required_source_artifact_classes\"],\ntests/test_wave_structure_analysis.py:67:            phase_gradient[\"required_source_artifact_classes\"],\ntests/test_wave_structure_analysis.py:75:            curvature[\"required_source_artifact_classes\"],\ntests/test_wave_structure_analysis.py:159:                    \"required_source_artif