{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_24","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba README.md | sed -n '128,150p'\"","aggregated_output":"   128\tThe runner does two phases, both in parallel:\n   129\t\n   130\t1. Specialize each generic review prompt for this repository.\n   131\t2. Run each specialized prompt to generate a senior-dev ticket pack.\n   132\t\n   133\tBy default artifacts land under `agent_tickets/review_runs/<timestamp>/`,\n   134\tincluding:\n   135\t\n   136\t- `specialization/<prompt-set>/specialized_prompt.md`\n   137\t- `reviews/<prompt-set>/tickets.md`\n   138\t- `combined_tickets.md`\n   139\t- `summary.json`\n   140\t\n   141\tUseful options:\n   142\t\n   143\t- `make review-tickets REVIEW_TICKETS_ARGS='--dry-run'`\n   144\t- `make review-tickets REVIEW_TICKETS_ARGS='--prompt-set efficiency_and_modularity'`\n   145\t- `make review-tickets REVIEW_TICKETS_ARGS='--specializer-model <model> --review-model <model>'`\n   146\t\n   147\tTo implement the resulting tickets as a review-aware backlog, run:\n   148\t\n   149\t```bash\n   150\tmake review-backlog REVIEW_BACKLOG_ARGS='--review-run-dir agent_tickets/review_runs/<timestamp>'\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
